{# Changelog — English. Keep newest release at the TOP.
   Badge convention: badge-success = New, badge-info = Improved, badge-warning = Fixed.
   When you add a release here, mirror it in de.html.twig. #}
<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">{{ 'static.changelog.title'|trans }}</h1>
<p class="mt-2 text-base-content/70">{{ 'static.changelog.lead'|trans }}</p>

<div class="mt-8 space-y-10">

  <section>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">19 June 2026</h2>
      <span class="badge badge-info badge-soft">Update</span>
    </div>
    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-success badge-sm shrink-0">New</span>
        <span>Tap any <strong>photo</strong> to open it full-size in a <strong>lightbox</strong> — page through a bookcase’s photos with the next/previous buttons, the arrow keys or a swipe.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-info badge-sm shrink-0">Improved</span>
        <span>The <strong>Guide</strong> now explains how to <strong>install OpenBookCase as an app</strong> (home screen / desktop) — including the not-so-obvious steps on Android and iPhone — and how to enable location access on iPhone &amp; iPad so the <strong>“Locate me”</strong> button works.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">18 June 2026</h2>
      <span class="badge badge-warning badge-soft">Fix</span>
    </div>
    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-warning badge-sm shrink-0">Fixed</span>
        <span>Opening times can be added and edited again: the editor’s “Opening times” section now has an <strong>Add opening time</strong> button, so you can set “24/7” or specific hours — including on brand-new entries. Removing an opening time sticks now, too.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-warning badge-sm shrink-0">Fixed</span>
        <span>The <strong>entry counter</strong> in the menu bar is accurate again (one entry had a broken coordinate that left it off the map) and now ticks up <strong>instantly</strong> when you add a bookcase, without needing a page reload.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">17 June 2026</h2>
      <span class="badge badge-info badge-soft">Update</span>
    </div>
    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-success badge-sm shrink-0">New</span>
        <span>The List page can now be sorted by “Added” to show the latest community additions first, each with the date it was added. (Bulk OpenStreetMap imports are left out of this view.)</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-success badge-sm shrink-0">New</span>
        <span>Apply for <strong>API access</strong> from your profile — developers can request an OAuth&nbsp;2.0 key to build apps on the OpenBookCase data (reviewed by an admin, with a built-in back-and-forth).</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-success badge-sm shrink-0">New</span>
        <span>A new <strong>Public API</strong> (<code>/api/v1</code>): open read endpoints (map area, single entry, photos, wishlist) plus OAuth-secured write endpoints (add/edit/move/delete entries, upload photos, wishlist, watchlist, home location). A <a class="link link-primary" href="{{ path('app_developers') }}">For&nbsp;developers</a> page under Info documents it with examples.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-success badge-sm shrink-0">New</span>
        <span>An <strong>admin area</strong> for reviewing, approving, denying and revoking API-access applications (admins only).</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">15 June 2026</h2>
      <span class="badge badge-info badge-soft">Update</span>
    </div>
    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-success badge-sm shrink-0">New</span>
        <span>Install OpenBookCase as an app on your phone or computer (“Add to Home Screen”) — it opens in its own window and always shows live data.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-success badge-sm shrink-0">New</span>
        <span>“Follow me” on the map: a new button live-tracks your location and keeps the map centred as you move. Tap again, or pan the map, to stop.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-warning badge-sm shrink-0">Fixed</span>
        <span>Location now works inside the installed app on iPhone, with a clear hint pointing you to Settings if location access is blocked.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-warning badge-sm shrink-0">Fixed</span>
        <span>The data export on the List page no longer fails on the full dataset — it is now streamed instead of built all at once.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-success badge-sm shrink-0">New</span>
        <span>The export can now be downloaded compressed (<code>.json.gz</code>) — a much smaller file for the full dataset.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-info badge-sm shrink-0">Improved</span>
        <span>Downloading the data export now shows the usage terms first (ODbL licence, OpenStreetMap attribution, no re-import into OSM) — the download starts once you agree.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">14 June 2026</h2>
      <span class="badge badge-primary badge-soft">Initial release</span>
    </div>
    <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
      <li class="flex flex-wrap items-start gap-2">
        <span class="badge badge-success badge-sm shrink-0">New</span>
        <span>First public release of OpenBookCase 2.0: search the map for public bookcases and give-boxes, view details and photos, manage your wishlist, rate locations, and add or reposition entries — with a multi-language interface and a light/dark theme.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

</div>
